name: Serotonin-Dopamine Plant
description: Being over decade busy with analog photography I was occasionally shocked how accidentally perfect may two frames fall over each other when you unintentionally run the same film through your camera twice. This overlapping would give another dimension and meaning to what was photographed, as if invisible kapellmeister had his own plan to it, far beyond my own intention. In this series "DOUBLE DREAM STRAINS" I tried to recreate this "lucky accident" effect digitally merging images together.
